title: How the 2022 Midterms Became a Squeaker
description: Interviews with more than 70 current and former officials show the outside forces — and miscalculations and infighting — that led to an improbable, still-undecided election.
media:credit: T.J. Kirkpatrick for The New York Times
media:description: Defying historical precedent, control of Congress remains too close to call days after the midterm elections.
